24/08/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Serbian Justice Minister Zoran Stojkovic presented the UN tribunal Tuesday (23 August) with government guarantees for the provisional release of former Yugoslav Army chief Nebojsa Pavkovic. He is charged with war crimes in Kosovo from 1998-1999. Stojkovic assured the trial chamber that Pavkovic, who surrendered to the tribunal in April after a lengthy delay, would appear before The Hague tribunal as soon as his trial begins.
In other news Tuesday, the Serbian Interior Ministry announced that it received a letter from the Spanish Embassy in Belgrade, praising police for the recent arrest of Abdelmajid Bouchar, a major suspect in the March 2004 Madrid train bombings. The letter expressed appreciation for the professionalism demonstrated in the case. (Beta, Tanjug - 23/08/05)
